  "text": "If fatty acid sensing systems activated when levels of specific fatty acid rise, what happens in those systems when levels of fatty acids fall? It is not possible to decrease the levels of a particular fatty acid. The only available studies in mammals used pharmacological treatments inhibiting lipolysis to induce a general decline in levels of all circulating fatty acids, which coincided with decreased activity of fatty acid sensing systems [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . A similar experimental approach in rainbow trout resulted in an inhibition of fatty acid sensing mechanisms in hypothalamus associated with the activation of the hypothalamus-pituitary-interrenal (HPI) axis [CITATION_3] .",
